# Same-file call: `main` calls `greet`, both defined in Greet.swift.
# Proves Tier-B same-file Scoped resolution: the `greet()` call on line 6
# resolves to the `func greet` definition on line 1, not fanning out to any
# external same-named symbol. Swift captures non-private top-level functions
# as Definition bindings (visibility gate in is_visible: no `private`/`fileprivate` modifier).
Greet.swift:6 Call Greet.swift:1
